properties.headline: Wind Chill Warning issued January 7 at 5:28AM AKST until January 7 at 6:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Dangerously cold wind chills to 65 below occuring. The
dangerously cold wind chills will cause frostbite in as little
as 10 minutes to exposed skin.

* WHERE...Western Arctic Coast.

* WHEN...Now to 6 PM this evening.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...East winds 15 mph along with very cold wind
chills will continue through this afternoon. Winds are expected
to diminish this evening.
properties.instruction:
A Wind Chill Warning means the combination of very cold air and
sustained wind speeds of 15 mph or more will create dangerously
low wind chill values. Frost bite can occur quickly and even
hypothermia or death if precautions are not taken.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM AKST THIS EVENING
